org.dockbox.selene.core.util.events

Class AbstractEventParamProcessor<A extends Annotation>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dockbox.selene.core.util.events.AbstractEventParamProcessor<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - The annotation type the processor applies to.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FaweSourceProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractEventParamProcessor<A extends Annotation>
extends Object
    A low level type used to process a given Annotation type. Typically this is only used by IWrapper implementations to populate, filter, or skip parameter arguments.

      • process

        @Nullable
public abstract @Nullable Object process(@Nullable
                                                    @Nullable Object object,
                                                    A annotation,
                                                    org.dockbox.selene.core.objects.events.Event event,
                                                    Parameter parameter,
                                                    IWrapper wrapper)
                                             throws org.dockbox.selene.core.exceptions.SkipEventException
        Processes the given object based on available information in the given Annotation, Event, Parameter} and/or IWrapper. If the parameter does not meet expectations, or should not be used in a given listener method, SkipEventException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to process.
        annotation - The annotation containing the definition of how the processor should act.
        event - The event for which the listener can be invoked.
        parameter - The parameter on which the annotation is applied.
        wrapper - The IWrapper which contains the invoking definition.
        Returns:
        The processed object
        Throws:
        org.dockbox.selene.core.exceptions.SkipEventException - Indicates the event listener should be skipped.
